From cd847716ef5057de9a05e1ff3bacdbadd8c90381 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 17 May 2026 00:34:10 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add LLM integration, streaming SSE, new agents, and improved
 test coverage

- Wire OpenAI and Anthropic providers via LangChain (src/llm/provider.py);
  agents gracefully fall back to deterministic logic when no API key is set
- Add CodingAgent (generate/review/explain modes) and SummarizationAgent
  (concise/detailed/bullet/executive styles) with extractive fallback
- Add POST /{agent_name}/stream SSE endpoint for token-by-token streaming
- Extend AgentFactory and main.py to pass llm instance to all agents and
  register coding_agent + summarization_agent by default
- Add 58 new tests: test_llm_provider, test_new_agents, test_agents_with_llm,
  integration streaming tests (215 total, all passing)
- Add Makefile with install/run/dev/test/lint/format targets
- Add scripts/start_dev.sh with .env validation and mock-mode warnings
- Update .env.example with LLM_PROVIDER, model, temperature, CORS vars
- Update requirements.txt with langchain-core, langchain-openai, langchain-anthropic

https://claude.ai/code/session_015MZ1vesqZFZxBLU7KtdCUj
